cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.SD

The paper introduces a computational model of evolvability and discusses its implications for biological and cultural evolution. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the model is computational and involves evolutionary processes. Additionally, the paper discusses the acceleration of evolutionary pace, which could relate to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses trends in evolution, which could relate to cs.SD (Software Development and Programming).
